<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-05-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-05-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="829" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d829">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 882.20.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 10.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-05-25">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 25, 1911</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your No. 10
                            (Diplomatic) of the 17th ultimo, in which you transmit copy of a note
                            received by you from the Liberian Secretary of State reminding this
                            Government of its intention to appoint United States Army officers for
                            service on the Liberian Frontier Force and requesting that Lieutenant B.
                            O. Davis, Military Attaché to the American Legation at Monrovia, be
                            detailed for such service as senior officer, if not incompatible with
                            the regulations of the Army.</p>
                        <p>In reply you are informed that the matter will receive due consideration
                            at the proper time.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>